17 computation and canvassing provided for in subsection (a) of this Code section and shall
18 be open to the public. For the purpose of such a manual recount, the superintendent may
19 organize his or her assistants into sections, each of whom may simultaneously proceed
20 with the manual recount provided for by this subsection.
21 (2) The results of such manual recount shall be unofficial, but if the results of such a
22 manual recount indicate a discrepancy with the official results of the computation,
23 canvassing, and tabulation provided for in this Code section, any such discrepancy shall
24 be addressed as provided for in subsections (b) through (h) of this Code section.
25 (3) The manual recount provided for in this subsection shall in no way delay or inhibit
26 the superintendent from complying with any requirements of this chapter. If an ongoing
27 manual recount will prevent a superintendent from meeting any of the requirements of
28 any provision of this chapter, such recount shall be immediately terminated."
29 SECTION 2.
30 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
